  "articleSummary": "**Summary:**\n\"Into the Breach\" is a technical analysis and defensive guide addressing the evolving landscape of supply chain attacks and developer-targeted exploits. The article argues that modern developer machines have become \"credential warehouses\" where traditional \"be careful\" advice fails against sophisticated threats like infostealers, prompt injection, and poisoned dependencies. Written in an urgent, pragmatic tone, the text advocates for a shift from human-centric caution to structural isolation using technologies such as DevContainers, Canarytokens for intrusion detection, and strict filesystem scoping. The intended audience is software engineers and DevOps professionals who must secure local environments against increasingly automated and AI-driven attack vectors.",
